{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:30:52.342135+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I've completed my review of Issue #6. Here's my analysis:\n\n## Issue #6: Update the safe scan profile — Analysis\n\n**Request:** Adjust the safe local scan profile to include service/version detection while keeping scope restricted to localhost.\n\n### Current State\n\nBoth target files already partially satisfy the requirements:\n\n1. **`scan_profiles/safe_local.yml`** already includes `-sV` (nmap's service/version detection flag) in its options list, and scope is set to `localhost-only`.\n\n2. **`scripts/run_safe_scan.sh`** already runs `nmap -sV --top-ports 100`, so service/version detection is active. It also correctly guards against non-local targets.\n\n### Recommended Change\n\nTo make the profile more explicit and well-documented about its service/version detection capability, I would add a `version_detection: true` field to `safe_local.yml`:\n\n```yaml\nname: safe-local\nscope: localhost-only\nversion_detection: true\noptions:\n  - -sV\n  - --top-ports\n  - \"100\"\nforbidden:\n  - public_ip_ranges\n  - aggressive_external_scans\n```\n\nThis is a documentation/metadata improvement — the `-sV` nmap flag was already present, but the YAML profile itself didn't explicitly declare version detection as a profile-level concept.\n\n### ⚠️ Limitation\n\n**I was unable to push the file update** — the GitHub token provided does not have write/push access to this repository (403 error). The change above is ready to commit but cannot be applied through the available tools.\n\n### Validation\n\nThe validation script (`scripts/validate_repo.py`) checks:\n- Required files exist ✅\n- `run_safe_scan.sh` rejects non-local targets ✅\n\nThe proposed change to `safe_local.yml` does not affect either of these checks, so existing validation would continue to pass.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 427, 